<subSubSection id="B4F06548B11FA13FEBADFC90E2B0FCFB" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="FC5536C3B11FA13FEBADFC90E2B0FCFB" blockId="19.[151,1436,833,1182]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B11FA13FEBADFC90E15AFCDF" bold="true" box="[151,304,833,858]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from scattered localities in the Succulent Karoo Biome in the Little Namaqualand region of the Northern Cape Province (
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B11FA13FEAE5FCB7E21AFCFB" author="Bauer" box="[479,624,870,894]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Bates, M. F. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2014 a) Afroedura halli (Hewitt, 1935). In: Bates, M. F., Branch, W. R., Bauer, A. M., Burger, M., Marais, J., Alexander, G. J. &amp; de Villiers, M. (Eds.), Atlas and Red List of the Reptiles of South Africa, Lesotho and Swaziland. Suricata, 1. South African National Biodiversity Institute, Pretoria, pp. 91 - 92." type="journal article" year="2014" yearSuffix="a">
Bauer 
<number id="4A2224E4B11FA13FE910FCB7E20EFCFB" box="[554,612,870,894]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="2014.0">2014</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation id="64D12A46B11FA13FE9BDFCB4E2A7FCFB" box="[647,717,869,894]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1165,1187]" captionTargetBox="[181,1379,205,1164]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[172,1393,177,1165]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 4. Map of southern Africa showing the approximate distributional ranges of previously described species of Afroedura. Red dots represent localities sampled for the genetic portion of the study. Ranges based on Branch (1998) and Bates et al. (2014) as well as unpublished data. Taxon names follow the conclusions of this paper. Area demarcated by a dashed line is presented in more detail in Figure 6." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/250499/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
Fig. 
<number id="4A2224E4B11FA13FE986FCB7E2A7FCFB" box="[700,717,870,894]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B4F06548B11FA13FEBFDFC58E11EFB1B" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FC5536C3B11FA13FEBFDFC58E11EFB1B" blockId="19.[151,1436,833,1182]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B11FA13FEBFDFC58E151FC27" bold="true" box="[199,315,905,930]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B11FA13FEA7BFC58E182FC27" author="Haacke" box="[321,488,905,930]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Haacke, W. D. (1965) Additional notes on the Herpetology of South West Africa with descriptions of two new subspecies of geckos. Cimbebasia, 11, 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1965">
Haacke (
<number id="4A2224E4B11FA13FEA9EFC58E18AFC27" box="[420,480,905,930]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1965.0">1965</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, in describing 
<taxonomicName id="3BEA4D40B11FA13FE9B1FC5BE313FC24" box="[651,889,906,930]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="africana" subSpecies="tirasensis">
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B11FA13FE9B1FC5BE313FC24" box="[651,889,906,930]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">A. africana tirasensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="3BEA4D40B11FA13FEF3AFC5BE4DBFC24" box="[1024,1201,906,929]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="namaquensis">
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B11FA13FEF3AFC5BE4DBFC24" box="[1024,1201,906,929]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">A. namaquensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="3BEA4D40B11FA13FEEBEFC5BE09CFC43" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B11FA13FEEBEFC5BE09CFC43" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">A. africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and it has maintained this rank since (
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B11FA13FE98FFC7FE33CFC43" author="Mertens" box="[693,854,942,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Mertens, R. (1971) Die Herpetofauna Sudwest - Afrikas. Abhandlungen der Senckenbergischen naturforschenden Gesellschaft, 529, 1 - 110." type="journal article" year="1971">
Mertens 
<number id="4A2224E4B11FA13FE821FC7FE33CFC43" box="[795,854,942,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1971.0">1971</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B11FA13FE85EFC7CE39DFC43" author="Branch" box="[868,1015,941,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Branch, W. R. (1981) An annotated checklist of the lizards of the Cape Province, South Africa. Annals of the Cape Provincial Museums (Natural History), 13, 141 - 167." type="journal article" year="1981">Branch 1981</bibRefCitation>
, 1988, 
<number id="4A2224E4B11FA13FEF76FC7FE4EDFC43" box="[1100,1159,942,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1998.0">1998</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B11FA13FEFAEFC7CE526FC43" author="Onderstall" box="[1172,1356,941,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Onderstall, D. (1984) Descriptions of two new subspecies of Afroedura pondolia (Hewitt) and a discussion of species groups within the genus (Reptilia: Gekkonidae). Annals of the Transvaal Museum, 33, 497 - 509." type="journal article" year="1984">
Onderstall 
<number id="4A2224E4B11FA13FEE2BFC7FE526FC43" box="[1297,1356,942,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B11FA13FEE63FC7FE08AFC6F" author="Bauer" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Bates, M. F. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2014 a) Afroedura halli (Hewitt, 1935). In: Bates, M. F., Branch, W. R., Bauer, A. M., Burger, M., Marais, J., Alexander, G. J. &amp; de Villiers, M. (Eds.), Atlas and Red List of the Reptiles of South Africa, Lesotho and Swaziland. Suricata, 1. South African National Biodiversity Institute, Pretoria, pp. 91 - 92." type="journal article" year="2014" yearSuffix="a">
Bauer 
<number id="4A2224E4B11FA13FEBADFC03E0B9FC6F" box="[151,211,978,1002]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="2014.0">2014</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
), although chiefly because this poorly known taxon has not been reviewed subsequently. Under modern species concepts, the differences between the supposed subspecies of 
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B11FA13FE8EDFC27E41EFB8B" box="[983,1140,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">A. africanaâ€”</emphasis>
including precloacal pore counts, presence of internasal granules, gular scale counts, and color pattern (
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B11FA13FEF2CFBC8E4C4FBB7" author="Haacke" box="[1046,1198,1049,1074]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Haacke, W. D. (1965) Additional notes on the Herpetology of South West Africa with descriptions of two new subspecies of geckos. Cimbebasia, 11, 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1965">
Haacke 
<number id="4A2224E4B11FA13FEF4FFBC8E4C4FBB7" box="[1141,1198,1049,1074]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1965.0">1965</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) would generally be accepted as evidence of specific distinctness, especially in light of the large disjunctions between the forms and their likely low vagility (
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B11FA13FEA90FBB3E2AAFBFF" author="Mouton" box="[426,704,1121,1146]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Mouton, P. le F. N. &amp; Mostert, D. P. (1985) Description of a new species of Afroedura (Loveridge) (Reptilia: Gekkonidae) from the south - western Cape. South African Journal of Zoology, 20, 246 - 249." type="journal article" year="1985">
Mouton &amp; Mostert 
<number id="4A2224E4B11FA13FE9BFFBB0E2AAFBFF" box="[645,704,1121,1146]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B11FA13FE9F1FBB0E319FBFF" author="Jacobsen" box="[715,883,1121,1146]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Jacobsen, N. H. G. (1997) Family Gekkonidae, Genus Afroedura. In: Van Wyk, J. H. (Ed.), Proceedings of the FitzSimons Commemorative Symposium, South African Lizards: 50 years of Progress and Third H. A. A. Symposium on African Herpetology, Transvaal Museum, Pretoria, South Africa, 11 - 15 October 1993. Herpetological Association of Africa, Stellenbosch, pp. 34 - 39." type="journal article" year="1997">
Jacobsen 
<number id="4A2224E4B11FA13FE80DFBB3E319FBFF" box="[823,883,1122,1146]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). On this basis we here recognize this taxon at the rank of full species.
</paragraph>
